{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:41:27.452275+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've completed my analysis of Issue #5. Unfortunately, I'm unable to push the changes because the personal access token doesn't have write permissions to the repository (both `create_or_update_file` and `push_files` returned 403 errors).\n\nHere's a summary of what I found and what needs to be done:\n\n## Issue #5: Update Installation Prerequisites\n\n**Files to review:** `docs/installation.md` and `sidebars.js`\n\n### Current State\n\n1. **`docs/installation.md`** — Contains minimal content (just a one-liner: \"Install Node.js and package dependencies before building the site.\")\n2. **`sidebars.js`** — Already correctly references `'installation'` in the sidebar configuration. ✅ No changes needed.\n\n### Proposed Changes\n\nOnly `docs/installation.md` needs updating. Here's the expanded content I prepared:\n\n```markdown\n---\nid: installation\ntitle: Installation\n---\n\n# Installation\n\nBefore setting up the project, ensure the following prerequisites are installed on your system:\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js** (version 18 or later) — required to run the Docusaurus development server and build the site.\n- **npm** (version 9 or later) — used to manage project dependencies.\n- **Git** — used to clone the repository.\n\nYou can verify your installed versions by running:\n\n```bash\nnode --version\nnpm --version\ngit --version\n```\n\n## Install Dependencies\n\nClone the repository and install the project dependencies:\n\n```bash\ngit clone <repository-url>\ncd <project-directory>\nnpm install\n```\n\n## Run Locally\n\nStart the local development server:\n\n```bash\nnpm start\n```\n\nThe site will be available at `http://localhost:3000` by default.\n```\n\n### Validation\n\nThe `sidebars.js` already includes `'installation'` in the sidebar and the validation script (`python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`) doesn't specifically check `docs/installation.md` content — it only checks for the existence of required files and proper `module.exports` in JS config files. The proposed change preserves the frontmatter `id: installation` so navigation continues to work correctly.\n\n### Limitation\n\nI was unable to commit the change due to a **403 permission error** — the access token does not have write access to this repository. A maintainer would need to apply these changes or grant the token push access.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 529, "prompt_tokens": 9695, "total_tokens": 10224, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 22, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9280, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000674163, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000213933, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00046023}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780965672-4mp5hM4hT0C33aqDnJTI", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9d3-8699-7e03-8c7d-d98c6de2dd3f-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9695, "output_tokens": 529, "total_tokens": 10224, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9280}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 22}}}}]}}}
